    explanation: `The BOD₅ test is the standard method for measuring biodegradable organic matter in wastewater. Procedure: (1) Dilute the sample with oxygen-saturated dilution water. (2) Measure the initial DO. (3) Incubate at 20°C in the dark for 5 days. (4) Measure the final DO. (5) BOD₅ (mg/L) = (initial DO - final DO) × dilution factor. The test measures the oxygen consumed by aerobic microorganisms as they degrade biodegradable organic matter. Typical values: raw sewage 150–300 mg/L; secondary effluent < 20 mg/L (Ontario limit typically 15–25 mg/L). The 5-day period represents approximately 68% of the ultimate BOD (BODu) at 20°C.`,
    difficulty: "medium",
