    correct: 1,
    explanation: `BOD vs COD: (1) BOD — measures oxygen consumed by microorganisms degrading biodegradable organic matter over 5 days. Slow (5 days), affected by nitrification (unless inhibited), measures only biodegradable fraction. (2) COD — measures oxygen equivalent of all oxidizable organic matter using potassium dichromate (K₂Cr₂O₇) in hot acid. Fast (2–3 hours), not affected by toxicity or nitrification, measures both biodegradable and non-biodegradable organics. COD is always ≥ BOD. The BOD/COD ratio indicates biodegradability: > 0.5 = readily biodegradable; 0.3–0.5 = moderately biodegradable; < 0.3 = poorly biodegradable (industrial wastewater). COD is used for rapid process control and to estimate BOD using the BOD/COD ratio.`,
