    correct: 1,
    explanation: `A Class 3 plant's effluent monitoring program is specified in the ECA and typically includes: (1) Core parameters — BOD₅, TSS, ammonia-nitrogen, total phosphorus, pH, fecal coliforms or E. coli, DO, temperature. (2) Nutrient parameters (if required) — total nitrogen, nitrate-nitrogen, total Kjeldahl nitrogen. (3) Metals — if industrial contributions are present. (4) Specific organics — if industrial contributions include organic chemicals. (5) Flow — continuous measurement. Monitoring frequency varies: daily for flow and some parameters; weekly or monthly for others. All results must be reported to the MECP per the ECA schedule. Effluent limits are set to protect the receiving water body based on its assimilative capacity.`,
