    correct: 1,
    explanation: `Total phosphorus (TP) analysis involves two steps: (1) Digestion — convert all phosphorus forms (organic, polyphosphate, orthophosphate) to orthophosphate using persulphate digestion (autoclave at 121°C) or acid digestion. (2) Colorimetric measurement — measure orthophosphate using the ascorbic acid method (molybdate blue, λ = 880 nm) or the vanadomolybdate method (λ = 420 nm). The ascorbic acid method is more sensitive and preferred for low concentrations (< 1 mg/L). For effluent compliance monitoring (TP < 0.3–1.0 mg/L), the ascorbic acid method is typically required. Orthophosphate (SRP) can be measured without digestion using the same colorimetric methods. All methods must be performed according to Standard Methods for the Examination of Water and Wastewater.`,
