    correct: 1,
    explanation: `TKN (total Kjeldahl nitrogen) analysis: (1) Digestion — the sample is digested with hot concentrated H₂SO₄ and a catalyst (copper sulphate, mercury, or selenium); organic nitrogen is converted to NH₄⁺. Note: nitrate and nitrite are NOT converted by Kjeldahl digestion and are NOT included in TKN. (2) Distillation — the digest is made alkaline with NaOH, and ammonia is steam-distilled into a boric acid receiver. (3) Titration — the distillate is titrated with H₂SO₄ to measure the ammonia. TKN = organic nitrogen + ammonia-nitrogen. Total nitrogen = TKN + nitrate-nitrogen + nitrite-nitrogen. TKN is used to assess the nitrogen load entering the plant and to calculate the nitrogen available for biological treatment. Effluent TKN is used to verify nitrification performance.`,
