    correct: 1,
    explanation: `Metals in wastewater exist in multiple forms: dissolved (ionic), colloidal, and particulate (associated with suspended solids). For total metals analysis: (1) Acid digestion — the sample is digested with hot concentrated acid (HNO₃, HCl, or aqua regia) to dissolve all particulate and colloidal metals, converting them to dissolved ionic forms. (2) Measurement — the digested sample is analyzed by AAS (flame or graphite furnace) or ICP-OES/ICP-MS. For dissolved metals, the sample is filtered (0.45 μm) before analysis without digestion. The distinction between total and dissolved metals is important for regulatory compliance and for understanding metals fate in the treatment process. Biosolids metals analysis requires complete digestion to ensure all metals are measured.`,
    difficulty: "hard",
