    correct: 1,
    explanation: `Tertiary treatment is required at Class 3 plants to meet stringent effluent limits for receiving waters with limited assimilative capacity. Common tertiary processes: (1) Tertiary filtration — granular media (sand, anthracite) or membrane filtration to remove residual TSS and BOD. (2) UV disinfection — inactivates pathogens without chemical residuals. (3) Chemical phosphorus removal — alum or ferric chloride addition to achieve TP < 0.3–1.0 mg/L. (4) Biological nutrient removal (BNR) — nitrogen and phosphorus removal through nitrification/denitrification and EBPR. (5) Membrane bioreactor (MBR) — combines biological treatment with membrane filtration for high-quality effluent. Tertiary treatment significantly increases capital and operating costs but is necessary to protect sensitive receiving waters.`,
