    correct: 1,
    explanation: `NPSH is critical for preventing cavitation in centrifugal pumps: (1) NPSHa (available) — the absolute pressure at the pump suction minus the vapour pressure of the liquid: NPSHa = (P_atm + P_static - P_friction - P_vapour) / ρg. Factors reducing NPSHa: high suction lift, long suction pipe (friction losses), high liquid temperature (higher vapour pressure), high altitude (lower atmospheric pressure). (2) NPSHr (required) — specified by the pump manufacturer; varies with flow rate (increases at higher flows). (3) Cavitation — occurs when NPSHa < NPSHr; liquid vaporizes at the pump inlet, forming vapour bubbles that collapse violently as pressure increases, causing noise (crackling/grinding), vibration, reduced performance, and impeller erosion. (4) Prevention — ensure NPSHa > NPSHr + safety margin (typically 0.5–1.0 m); reduce suction lift, minimize suction pipe losses, maintain wet well level above minimum.`,
