    explanation: `Mechanical seal replacement is a common maintenance task for centrifugal pumps: (1) LOTO — lock out and tag out the motor; verify zero energy state. (2) Drain — drain the pump casing and suction line if necessary. (3) Disassembly — remove coupling guard, disconnect flexible coupling, remove pump casing bolts, remove casing, remove impeller (note: left-hand thread on some pumps), remove shaft sleeve if present. (4) Seal removal — slide the rotating seal component off the shaft; remove the stationary seat from the seal chamber. (5) Inspection — inspect the shaft and shaft sleeve for wear or scoring; replace if damaged. (6) New seal installation — clean the seal chamber; install the new stationary seat (use the installation tool provided, do not touch the lapped face); slide the rotating component onto the shaft (lubricate the rubber bellows with water or soapy water, not petroleum-based lubricants); compress the spring to the correct installation length. (7) Reassembly — reverse the disassembly steps; check pump-motor alignment. (8) Startup — start the pump and check for leaks at the seal; a small amount of weeping (< 1 drop/minute) is normal during break-in.`,
