    correct: 1,
    explanation: `Digester gas holders manage the mismatch between biogas production (relatively constant) and demand (variable): (1) Types — floating cover (rises and falls with gas volume, maintains constant pressure), fixed volume (pressure varies with gas production), membrane gas holders (flexible membrane). (2) Pressure — gas holders maintain a slight positive pressure (0.5–2.5 kPa) in the gas collection system; pressure relief valves protect against overpressure; vacuum relief valves prevent negative pressure (which could draw air into the system, creating an explosive mixture). (3) Condensate — biogas is saturated with water vapour; as it cools in pipes, condensate forms and must be drained from low points (condensate traps) to prevent gas line blockage. (4) Safety — flame arrestors prevent flame propagation back to the digester; pressure gauges and alarms monitor gas holder level; regular inspection for leaks (soap solution or gas detector). (5) Biogas utilization — gas holders allow biogas to be used in boilers or engines at a controlled rate, independent of production rate.`,
