    correct: 1,
    explanation: `Belt filter press (BFP) performance evaluation: (1) Cake dryness — measure % TS of the cake; target 15–25% for mixed sludge; low cake dryness indicates: insufficient polymer, belt tension too low, belt speed too high, sludge not suitable for BFP dewatering. (2) Solids capture — measure TSS in the filtrate; solids capture (%) = [1 - (filtrate TSS × filtrate flow) / (feed TSS × feed flow)] × 100; target > 90%; low capture indicates: polymer underdosing, belt blinding, or sludge characteristics. (3) Polymer consumption — measure polymer dose (kg/tonne DS); compare to design and historical data; increasing polymer consumption may indicate changing sludge characteristics. (4) Belt condition — inspect belts for blinding (clogged pores), tracking problems, tears, and wear; clean belts with high-pressure wash water. (5) Roller condition — inspect rollers for wear, corrosion, and bearing condition. (6) Throughput — measure feed flow and compare to design capacity; reduced throughput may indicate belt blinding or sludge characteristics.`,
