    correct: 1,
    explanation: `Fine-bubble diffuser evaluation: (1) Oxygen transfer efficiency (OTE) — off-gas testing measures the oxygen content of the air leaving the aeration tank and compares to inlet air; OTE (%) = (O₂ in - O₂ out) / O₂ in × 100. Clean water testing (ASCE standard) measures OTE in clean water under standard conditions. Declining OTE indicates diffuser fouling. (2) Diffuser pressure drop — measure the pressure at the blower discharge and at the diffuser headers; increasing pressure drop (> 0.5 kPa from baseline) indicates diffuser fouling. (3) Air flow distribution — use a pitot tube or flow meter to measure air flow to each diffuser grid; non-uniform distribution indicates partial blockage or header problems. (4) Visual inspection — during tank dewatering, inspect diffusers for: biological fouling (brown/black coating), mineral scaling (white calcium carbonate), grease accumulation, physical damage (cracks, tears in membrane diffusers). (5) Cleaning — membrane diffusers can be cleaned by air scouring (brief high-flow air purge), acid cleaning (citric acid or hydrochloric acid), or manual cleaning during tank dewatering.`,
