    correct: 1,
    explanation: `UV disinfection system performance evaluation: (1) UV transmittance (UVT) — measure regularly using a UV spectrophotometer (254 nm); UVT varies with effluent quality (TSS, colour, dissolved organics); low UVT reduces UV dose delivered. (2) UV intensity — UV sensors in the reactor measure the UV intensity; compare to the design minimum intensity; declining intensity indicates lamp aging or sleeve fouling. (3) UV dose — calculate from intensity and exposure time; verify that the dose meets the design requirement (typically 40–80 mJ/cm² for secondary effluent). (4) Effluent quality — measure fecal coliforms or E. coli; compare to the ECA limit; exceedances indicate insufficient UV dose. (5) Lamp age — track operating hours for each lamp; replace lamps before they reach the end of their rated life (8,000–12,000 hours) or when intensity drops below the minimum. (6) Sleeve fouling — measure UV intensity with and without sleeve cleaning; significant improvement after cleaning indicates fouling is reducing performance. (7) Bioassay testing — periodic testing with MS2 bacteriophage or Bacillus subtilis spores verifies the actual log reduction achieved.`,
